cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.MM. 

The paper deals with automatic affect recognition using auditory and visual modalities, which suggests that it could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories. 

- cs.SD (Sound) is the most likely category as the paper deals with speech and audio processing. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is also a likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and emotion recognition. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper uses deep neural networks for feature extraction and machine learning algorithms for emotion recognition. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible category as the paper also deals with visual modality and uses a deep residual network for feature extraction. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper deals with emotion recognition in multimedia data.
